liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: No late changes tonight. A big in and a big out for Collingwood, with Nick Daicos playing his first game since round 21 and Taylor Adams missing out due to an injury suffered at training. The Giants are unchanged from the team that beat Port Adelaide last weekend — what a luxury at this stage of the season. The subs are Jack Ginnivan for Collingwood and Xavier O'Halloran for GWS.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: The final teams and subs are in

children.content: A big in and a big out for Collingwood, with Nick Daicos playing his first game since round 21 and Taylor Adams missing out due to an injury suffered at training.
The Giants are unchanged from the team that beat Port Adelaide last weekend — what a luxury at this stage of the season.
The subs are Jack Ginnivan for Collingwood and Xavier O'Halloran for GWS.

image.altText: Nathan Cleary jogs

props.synopsis: The Panthers are looking to reach their fourth-straight NRL grand final, hosting the Storm at Stadium Australia in the preliminary final. Follow all the updates in our live blog.

title.children: The Panthers take on the Storm in the first NRL preliminary final

liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Panthers vs Storm starting line ups

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Craig Bellamy has rolled the dice a little — but not extravagantly with his line up tonight, with 19th man Bronson Garlick and Nelson Asofa-Solomona both coming into the starting line up after initially being named on the bench. Harry Grant and Christian Welch drop to the bench, while Tyran Wishart drops out of the 17 and is named as sub.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Melbourne make changes

children.content: Craig Bellamy has rolled the dice a little — but not extravagantly with his line up tonight, with 19th man Bronson Garlick and Nelson Asofa-Solomona both coming into the starting line up after initially being named on the bench.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: No late surprises for the Panthers, who are 1-17 as listed on Tuesday. Izack Tago and Jarome Luai both return from injury and will take their spot in the starting 13. Nathan Cleary is also deemed fit despite hurting his finger at training. Jack Cogger and Luke Garner return to the interchange.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Penrith lock in their starting line up

children.content: No late surprises for the Panthers, who are 1-17 as listed on Tuesday.
Izack Tago and Jarome Luai both return from injury and will take their spot in the starting 13.
Nathan Cleary is also deemed fit despite hurting his finger at training.
Jack Cogger and Luke Garner return to the interchange.
